    title: 'Scaling to $10M ARR: The First 5 Hires Every AI Founder Needs',
    summary: 'The blueprint for building a high-leverage team that can scale revenue 10x without 10x-ing the headcount.',
    aiSummary: 'To reach $10M ARR with a lean team, your first 5 hires should be "Force Multipliers": (1) A Product-Focused Engineer, (2) A Head of Distribution/Growth, (3) An Operations/Automation Architect, (4) A Technical Customer Success lead, and (5) A Full-Stack Designer. These roles focus on building systems that automate growth and support.',
    content: 'In the AI era, hiring is a liability, not an asset. To reach $10M ARR, you no longer need 100 people. You need a small group of "T-shaped" individuals who can own entire business functions. Hire #1 should be a Product-Focused Engineer who cares as much about the "why" as the "how." Hire #2 is a Head of Distribution who can build automated growth loops. Hire #3 is an Operations Architect whose job is to ensure the team never has to do the same task twice by building internal AI agents. Hire #4 is Technical Customer Success—someone who can write code to solve customer problems proactively. Hire #5 is a Full-Stack Designer who can own the entire user experience. This "Core 5" plus the founders can manage $10M+ in revenue by leveraging AI for everything from code generation to sales outreach.',
    founderTakeaway: 'Hire for systems, not tasks. Every hire should be tasked with automating their own role within the first year. If they can\'t build a system to handle their work, they aren\'t the right fit for an AI-first startup.',
