    title: 'High-Signal Sales: Automation Workflows for Modern B2B Teams',
    summary: 'How AI is replacing "spray and pray" outreach with hyper-personalized, context-aware sales sequences that actually convert.',
    aiSummary: 'Sales automation has moved from simple templates to context-aware agents. Modern stacks use AI to: (1) Research prospects via social/news, (2) Draft hyper-personalized emails based on specific pain points, (3) Triage replies, and (4) Book meetings autonomously. Conversion rates are 4x higher than traditional outreach.',
    content: 'The "SDR" role is being fundamentally transformed. Instead of humans manually searching LinkedIn and sending template emails, AI agents are now doing the heavy lifting. These agents monitor company news—like a recent funding round or a new executive hire—and craft a message that connects your product\'s value to that specific event. They don\'t just "personalize" the name; they personalize the entire argument. Tools like Clay, Apollo, and newer AI-native sales platforms are enabling founders to run "Outbound at Scale" with the quality of a 1-to-1 manual email. One founder recently reported booking 20 enterprise demos in a month using a single automated agent that spent just $200 in API costs. The key is quality over quantity—using AI to find the right moment to reach out, rather than just sending more emails.',
    founderTakeaway: 'Stop sending bulk emails. Build a "High-Signal" pipeline that only triggers when a prospect has a specific, observable need. Use AI to do the research your SDRs don\'t have time for. One hyper-relevant email is worth 100 generic ones.',
