    title: 'The Death of the Blue Link: How AI Search is Changing Consumer Behavior',
    summary: 'What Perplexity and SearchGPT mean for your content strategy and how to ensure your startup remains discoverable in an answer-first world.',
    aiSummary: 'Search is shifting from "links" to "answers." This means SEO strategies must evolve from keyword stuffing to "Authority Mining." AI search engines favor long-form, deeply researched, original content that provides definitive answers. Startups need to focus on becoming the "source of truth" for their niche to be cited by AI agents.',
    content: 'The traditional Google search experience is being challenged by "Answer Engines" like Perplexity and OpenAI\'s SearchGPT. For founders, this changes everything about distribution. In the old world, you optimized for keywords to get a click. In the new world, you optimize for "Authority" so an AI agent cites you as the definitive source. Consumer behavior is shifting toward asking complex questions and expecting synthesized answers. This means your content strategy should focus on original research, proprietary data reports, and deep technical guides—things an AI can\'t easily hallucinate or synthesize from generic sources. If your brand is cited in the "Sources" section of a Perplexity answer, that click is worth 10x more than a generic Google search click because the user is already high-intent.',
    founderTakeaway: 'Stop writing generic blog posts for SEO. Start publishing original data, case studies, and deep technical insights. Focus on becoming the primary source for your industry\'s most difficult questions. If you are the source of the data, the AI engines have to cite you.',
