    title: 'Leveraging AI for Product Analytics: Beyond Dashboarding',
    summary: 'How to use LLMs to find the "Hidden Aha Moments" in your user data that traditional analytics tools miss.',
    aiSummary: 'AI-powered analytics tools are moving from "What happened?" to "Why did it happen?". By feeding event streams into LLMs, founders can identify non-obvious correlations between user actions and long-term retention. This "Semantic Analytics" is uncovering product opportunities that would take a human analyst weeks to find.',
    content: 'Traditional analytics tools like Mixpanel and Amplitude are great at telling you your conversion rate. But they aren\'t good at telling you why a user decided to stay. A new wave of AI-native analytics tools is using LLMs to perform "Semantic Analysis" on user behavior. Instead of just looking at clicks, they look at the intent behind the clicks. They can identify patterns like "Users who use the AI feature three times in the first hour are 4x more likely to convert, but only if they get a high-quality result on the first try." This level of insight allows product teams to focus on the exact moments that drive value. Founders are now using these tools to automatically generate hypotheses for A/B tests, dramatically speeding up the product iteration cycle.',
    founderTakeaway: 'Your data has stories you can\'t see. Use an AI-augmented analytics tool to look for "retention correlations." Focus your development roadmap exclusively on the features that have the highest semantic connection to long-term user value.',
